(50, 6, 'Second Vivekananda Bridge (Nivedita Setu) Tollway Project Kolkata, West Bengal, India - Independent Consultancy (IC) Services', '<p>\r\n	This tollway project is envisaged as a 6.1 km long network comprising of 6 lane Extradosed Cable Stayed Bridge (main bridge length - 880m) and approach roadways (Kolkata side approach is 1.55km and &nbsp;Dankuni side approach is 3.66km consisting of viaduct structure as well as high embankments). The main bridge has 7 nos. spans each of 110 m and two 55 m end spans with width of 31m. This is a multi-span Extradosed Bridge, a hybrid structure combining elements of cable stayed and post tensioned segmental single-cell box girders of precast concrete. The special features of this Extradosed Bridge is that it has been designed with central suspended system having cables extending from both sides of the pylons and connected to the deck. Cast-in-place piers rest on well foundations in the form of circular caissons. 11 m diameter and average 45 m deep. In addition, a number of underpasses &amp; ROBs will be constructed along the approach roads.</p>\r\n', '14219295110.jpg', 'second-vivekananda-bridge-(nivedita-setu)-tollway-project-kolkata-west-bengal-india-independent-consultancy-(ic)-services', '2015-01-22 17:55:11', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(51, 6, 'Bridge over River Yamuna at Kalpi, India', '<p>\r\n	The 767 m long bridge across the river Yamuna at Kalpi has 85 m in-situ cantilever constructed spans pinned at their centers. &nbsp;In order not to detract from the graceful form of the spans which are 2.0 m deep at the center and 6.0 m deep at the supports, a light parapet was developed and precast to obtain a good finish and alignment.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The cantilever bridge required hollow rectangular piers; in addition, hollow triangular cut and ease waters were provided in view of the high flood velocities.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The resulting elongated hexagonal pier section was made to fuse gently at the top into the rectangular section, a departure from the conventional approach of making an abrupt and discordant change in pier section at high flood level. Consequently, the deck and piers also fuse gracefully.&nbsp;</p>', '14219295640.jpg', 'bridge-over-river-yamuna-at-kalpi-india', '2015-01-22 17:56:04', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(52, 6, 'Second Thane Creek Bridge, Mumbai, India', '<p>\r\n	In order to meet the future traffic demands on the link between Navi Mumbai and the mainland, a second bridge, 1845 m long is constructed across the Thane Creek. &nbsp;The bridge superstructure consists of two independent decks, each with a 3 lane carriage-way. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	To meet the hydraulic and navigation requirements the piers of the bridge are aligned with piers of existing road and Rail Bridge. &nbsp;This results in a span arrangement with a combination of 53.5 m and 107 m spans. &nbsp;A typical continuous unit is 321 m overall length with span arrangement of (53.5+2 x 107+53.5) m</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	To ensure durability under the severe aggressive environment, extensive treatment was given to components of superstructure as well as substructure. &nbsp;Open foundations in standing water, up to 9m depth, are provided at all the locations except abutment on Mumbai side which is a well (caisson) foundation.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	A novel cofferdam was in precast R.C.C. for the depth of clay at the bottom and was left behind after use. The upper hollow steel portion was recovered and was reused. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Sinking was carried out up to rock level by grabs excavating the marine clay within the cofferdam.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The foundation was keyed with hard rock by a downward projection in RCC from the shallow bottom plug.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	No explosives could be used for excavation in rock required for seating the foundation of the New Bridge, because the old bridge was in service during construction of the new one. &nbsp;Excavation in Rock was done by Pneumatic Chisels.</p>', '14219296240.jpg', 'second-thane-creek-bridge-mumbai-india', '2015-01-22 17:57:04', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(56, 6, 'Park Street flyover, Kolkata', '<p>\r\n	Length of the flyover is 795M including 97M approach on each side. It consists of single carriageway of 2 lanes. &nbsp;The Flyover comprises of 17 spans each 25M long + 2 spans each 48M long with box girders and one span 39M long in mid-span also with box girder. Foundation consists of 1000 mm dia RCC bored pile of average length 38M from the cut off level. Each pile is designed to carry 300 MT load, five piles on average from a pile cap over which steel pier with cross heads and I-girders are arranged to support a 300 mm (avg.) thick RCC deck slab. &nbsp;The Flyover is constructed over the busiest city road after relocating dry and wet utilities in addition to relocation of one Metro Airshaft Building, one Metro Exit Structure and one Metro Cover Slab exist within the ROW of the flyover. A diversion road of 1350 meters was constructed to accommodate the flyover.</p>\r\n', '14219301520.jpg', 'park-street-flyover-kolkata', '2015-01-22 18:05:52', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(55, 6, 'Motorable Suspension Bridge over river Lohit connecting Chequenty and Hawai', '<p>\r\n	<span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:\r\n115%;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\nmso-font-kerning:12.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;\r\nmso-bidi-language:AR-SA;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold">The single lane road suspension bridge over river Lohit is connecting Chequenty and Hawai town at Tezu district. The main suspension span of the bridge is 156.4 m and there are three nos. shore spans of 20m each at Hawai end. The bridge consists of steel suspension system with steel truss deck and steel towers supported on RCC foundations, RCC anchorage block, Return wall etc. The locations of the bridge are mountainous and rocky with fast flowing rivers. The scope of work included study of all data related to sub-soil investigation reports, hydraulic and geological data, selection of bridge type, detailed design and execution drawings, bill of quantities and cost estimates, inspection of fabrication etc.</span></p>\r\n', '14219300850.jpg', 'motorable-suspension-bridge-over-river-lohit-connecting-chequenty-and-hawai', '2015-01-22 18:04:45', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(57, 6, 'Benninganahalli Flyover, Bangalore', '<p>\r\n	This grade separator crosses the NH4 along the Outer RingRoad and has 3 approaches. The superstructure consists of two carriageways, of cast-in-situ continuous, RCC girder and slab type construction. Prestressed concrete box girders are provided for the Road Over Bridge portion and for the obligatory spans. A number of viaducts are provided with trestle type piers which are supported over pile foundations.</p>\r\n', '14219302410.jpg', 'benninganahalli-flyover-bangalore', '2015-01-22 18:07:21', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(58, 6, 'Hebbal Flyover, Bangalore', '<p>\r\n	India&#39;s longest flyover designed to decongest traffic at the junction of NH-7 and the recently completed Outer Ring Road. The looped grade separator designed by us allows for substantial decongestion which considerably alleviates the traffic problem as required by the Bangalore Development Authority, especially in view of the present traffic load flowing out of NH-7and the new Outer Ring Road, and also caters for future load likely to arise from the expected commissioning of Bangalore International Airport.</p>\r\n', '14219303420.jpg', 'hebbal-flyover-bangalore', '2015-01-22 18:09:02', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(59, 6, 'Kathipara Flyover, Chennai', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;NHAI along with the State Government of Tamil Nadu programmed to develop access to the Golden Quadrilateral (GQ) Corridor by providing free flow facilities in highly trafficked areas in Chennai. &nbsp;Pursuant to the above, the Tamil Nadu Road Development Company Limited (TNRDC) has initiated proposals to alleviate the traffic congestion at Kathipara Junction, entry and Exit Points of Chennai Airport on NH-45, NH-4 &ndash; IRR Junction at Koyambedu and at NH-205 &ndash; IRR Junction at Padi.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Kathipara Flyover involves design and construction of a clover leaf Interchange at the busy Kathipara intersection in the heart of Chennai city. The structural portion involves 600 m long dual 12.0 m wide decks for the main viaduct spans connecting the Inner Ring Road to the Airport. Four loops of approx. 200 m length each will connect to the main viaduct from the Guindy - Poonamallee Road. All the structural spans are resting on aesthetically shaped piers founded on open footings at 3 to 4 m depth. The total structural area of the grade separator is 16,750 sqm. Voided slab superstructure in PSC &amp; RCC have been adopted.</p>', '14219304110.jpg', 'kathipara-flyover-chennai', '2015-01-22 18:10:11', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(62, 3, 'NATURAL  DRAUGHT  COOLING  TOWERS for POWER PLANT (2X600MW) AT  KALISINDH  THERMAL POWER STATION', '<p>\r\n	The total height of the tower is 202m with basin diameter of 149.35m. The NDCT consists of a hyperbolic RCC shell that is supported on 60 pairs of RCC diagonal columns. The towers are in a high wind velocity &nbsp;(47m/s) &nbsp;zone &nbsp;making &nbsp;the design complex. For NDCTs it is more important to control the thickness of the shell to keep the quantities and the weight of the tower under control. The thickness &nbsp;to volume ratio in these towers is 0.003 which is comparable to an egg shell. An Aero Elastic &nbsp;Model &nbsp;was tested in a wind tunnel &nbsp;to confirm the design stresses. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	These natural draught cooling towers are the tallest in the world.</p>', '14219310180.jpg', 'natural-draught-cooling-towers-for-power-plant-(2x600mw)-at-kalisindh-thermal-power-station', '2015-01-22 18:20:18', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(63, 3, 'SIMHADRI COOLING TOWERS for POWER PLANT (2X500MW)', '<p class="BasicParagraph">\r\n	<span class="A3"><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\nArial">A separate cooling tower of 165 m height has been provided for each 500 MW power plant. The cooling capacity of the tower is 60,000 cu m/hr of sea water to be cooled from 43<sup>0</sup>C to 32<sup>0</sup>C at 27.8<sup>0</sup> C ambient wet bulb temperature &amp; 60% relative humidity.&nbsp;<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	</span></span><span style="font-family: Cambria, serif; font-size: 11pt;">The Simhadri Cooling Towers were the tallest towers in Asia in 2000.</span></p>\r\n', '14219310900.jpg', 'simhadri-cooling-towers-for-power-plant-(2x500mw)', '2015-01-22 18:21:30', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(64, 3, 'RCC PYLONS FOR THERMAL POWER PLANT (2 X 210 MW) AT VIJAYAWADA', '<p>\r\n	Two sets of four RCC Pylons, interconnected at the top by structural steel crown girders are used to support the two 8500 MT boilers for the thermal power plant. The four 67m high pylons rest on well foundations and are slipformed together for the entire height to maintain proper alignment. The RCC pylons reduce lateral deflections due to wind and earthquake. The steel crown girders having a total weight of 575 MT per unit are erected using an erection tower with a lifting system of interconnected hydraulic jacks and prestressing strands acting as suspenders.</p>\r\n', '14219311480.jpg', 'rcc-pylons-for-thermal-power-plant-(2-x-210-mw)-at-vijayawada', '2015-01-22 18:22:28', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(65, 3, 'DUL HASTI HYDROELECTRIC POWER PROJECT (3 X 130MW), JAMMU AND KASHMIR', '<p>\r\n	This hydro-electric power project consists of a diversion dam at &lsquo;Dul&rsquo; across the river Chenab and a Power House at &lsquo;Hasti&rsquo;. The concrete gravity dam of 185 m length and 65 m height has an ungated spillway of 40 m length and a gated spillway of 64 m length with four radial gates. The dam has four orifices designed for 8000 cumecs of discharge. Two intake tunnels originate from the intake tower located 150 m upstream of the dam, and lead to desilting basins. The 10.6 km long headrace tunnel with a drop of 235 m carries the water to the underground power house. The underground powerhouse accommodates 3 sets of Francis Turbines each coupled to a 130 MW generator.</p>\r\n', '14219312360.jpg', 'dul-hasti-hydroelectric-power-project-(3-x-130mw)-jammu-and-kashmir', '2015-01-22 18:23:56', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(66, 3, 'INDIRA SAGAR DAM, IRRIGATION AND HYDRO-ELECTRIC PROJECT, MADHYA PRADESH', '<p>\r\n	The Narmada Hydroelectric Development Corporation Limited ( joint venture of the National Hydroelectric Power Corporation and the Govt. of Madhya Pradesh) constructed the Indira Sagar Dam on the river Narmada. It is a concrete gravity dam, 653 m in length, with a maximum height of 92 m. The spillway portion of the dam consists of twenty, 20 m wide gated spillways with 21 piers. The spillway gates are of the sector type, and are lifted hydraulically. The gates are 20 m wide 17 m in height, and extend from pier to pier. Each pier is 5 m in width. Prestressed replaceable anchors are provided for the spillway gates.</p>\r\n', '14219313020.jpg', 'indira-sagar-dam-irrigation-and-hydro-electric-project-madhya-pradesh', '2015-01-22 18:25:02', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(67, 3, '275 m Tall Triple Steel Flue RC Chimney for 6 x 600 MW Sasan Ultra Mega Power Project, Madhya Pradesh  ', '<p>\r\n	Two numbers of 275 m tall triple steel flue RC chimneys with diameter Varying from 24 m on top and 36.7m at base and founded on annular raft are under construction at Sasan, India, for 4000MW Thermal Power Station.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Each chimney is designed to house three steel flues, each flue serving one of the three 660MW units. Chimney shell is designed for basic wind speed of 150 kmph. In order to reduce the effects of across wind loads fundamental frequency of the chimney shell is lowered by gradually increasing the thickness of shell in top portion. For seismic design, Chimney is located in Zone-III as per zoning given by IS:1893-2001, which is characterised by Maximum Considered Earthquake (MCE) ground acceleration of 0.16 g.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Each of the steel flue has inside diameter of 7.1 m. Steel flues are &lsquo;hung type&rsquo;and are suspended in segments from five intermediate platforms spaced 45m apart. Expansion compensators are provided at bottom of each flue segment to allow relative thermal movements between the steel flue and RC shell. The lateral restraints to ensure consistent deformations and transfer horizontal forces arising from wind and earthquake are provided at these platform levels. For achieving comfortable working conditions within the annular space between chimney and flues, temperature of air in this space is maintained below 450C.</p>', '14219313590.jpg', '275-m-tall-triple-steel-flue-rc-chimney-for-6-x-600-mw-sasan-ultra-mega-power-project-madhya-pradesh', '2015-01-22 18:25:59', '2015-01-22 18:27:00', '1', '', '', '', 0),
(68, 3, 'IDCTs at Ramagundam STPP (1 x 500 MW) ', '<p>\r\n	&bull; 2nos of IDCTs with counterflow configuration are provided for unit-7 (1x500MW) at Ramagundam TPS of NTPC.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; STUP provided Detailed Engineering to the contractor</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Each cooling tower is designed for water flow of 30,000m3/hr.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; No. of cells are 14 working + 2 standby in back to back arrangement.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The total tower dimensions are 30.3 m x 127.3 m.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Fill used &ndash; PP Grid &ndash; first time in India</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Commissioned in year 2004 and tested successfully.</p>', '14219314690.jpg', 'idcts-at-ramagundam-stpp-(1-x-500-mw)', '2015-01-22 18:27:49', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(69, 3, 'Water intake, transportation and other allied structures for Bakreswar Thermal Power Project (3 x 210 MW) of WBPDCL in West Bengal.', '<p>\r\n	The scope comprises design of 2.6 km water intake / transportation system, DM Plant, Clarified Water PH, Filter House, Filter Water PH, Filtration Bed, and pipe lines and pipe galleries</p>\r\n', '14219315400.jpg', 'water-intake-transportation-and-other-allied-structures-for-bakreswar-thermal-power-project-(3-x-210-mw)-of-wbpdcl-in-west-bengal', '2015-01-22 18:29:00', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(70, 8, 'Azimganj - Bhagirathi Bridge (Eastern Railways)', '<p>\r\n	Eastern Railway, India, proposed to connect the two railway stations at opposite side of river Hooghly, namely Murshidabad station and Azimganj station at 7.5 km apart by a new MBG single track line. The preliminary survey was undertaken by Eastern Railways in the year 2002. The project included &nbsp;construction &nbsp;of the 7.5km railway track including the 330 m long bridge across river Bhagirathi .</p>\r\n', '14219319590.jpg', 'azimganj-bhagirathi-bridge-(eastern-railways)', '2015-01-22 18:35:59', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(71, 8, 'Jogighopa Rail cum Road Bridge over River Brahmaputra, Assam', '<p>\r\n	The North-East Frontier Railways, in association with the Public Works Department of Assam, constructed the third bridge across the river Brahmaputra at Jogighopa. The bridge connects NH-31 and NH-37 forming a very important link between the north-east and the rest of India. The project consists of the construction of 13km of rail-cum-road and a 2.27 km long two tier steel bridge excluding approach viaducts. The span configuration of steel bridge portion is 19x120 m + 1x90m.</p>\r\n', '14219320000.jpg', 'jogighopa-rail-cum-road-bridge-over-river-brahmaputra-assam', '2015-01-22 18:36:40', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(72, 8, 'Railway Bridge over Vasai Creek, Maharashtra', '<p>\r\n	This bridge is 4km long with spans of 48.5m, each weighing 750 t.They are precast, shifted &amp; launched into position using entirely hand operated equipment and a simple barge. This was among the first examples of such large precast spans being used to construct a bridge for the Indian Railways.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Since the earlier bridge had corroded, special precautions have been taken in constructing the new bridge. Entire spans were totally precast on the shore, to achieve very high quality of construction.Thereafter the spans were lifted on to a specially designed barge by using the rising tide, were towed 3.5km to site and lowered in position using the falling tide.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The construction equipment engineered for the bridge was economical and suitable for use by a developing country contractor.</p>', '14219321090.jpg', 'railway-bridge-over-vasai-creek-maharashtra', '2015-01-22 18:38:29', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(73, 8, 'Electrified Double Track Railway Project from Rawang to Ipoh in Malaysia', '<p>\r\n	The stretch of assignment - Electrified Double Track Railway Project from Rawang to Ipoh is 180 km.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The project comprises audit of the railway alignment design &amp; drawing for the 110 km stretch from Rawang to Bidor based of an Permanent way manual &amp; technical specification (Statement Of Needs, SON) for Electrified Double Track and design speed of 160 km/ hr.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	SCL was involved in carrying out audit of alignment design report, audit of vertical &amp; horizontal alignment for 110 km electrified metre gauge double track rail having design speed of 160 km/ hr, audit of location and hydraulic levels of all railway bridges, audit of yard schematics, scaled yard drawings and coordinates of salient points of turn outs, vertical &amp; horizontal clearances of road bridges and preparation of report on technical &amp; safety deficiencies</p>', '14219322080.jpg', 'electrified-double-track-railway-project-from-rawang-to-ipoh-in-malaysia', '2015-01-22 18:40:08', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(74, 8, 'Rail-cum-Road bridge over river Damodar at Mejia in West Bengal', '<p>\r\n	Damodar Valley Corporation (DVC) transports coal by rail to their thermal power plant in Mejia through a captive railway system. The line carries 7000 tonnes of coal daily to meet the requirement of the 630 MW plant. This line crosses river Damodar near Raniganj. The bridge carries a 2-lane road of NH Standards and a B.G. railway track. The span arrangement is 15 x 48.5 M + 2 x 33 M (steel truss). The overall length of the bridge is 850m.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '14219322740.jpg', 'rail-cum-road-bridge-over-river-damodar-at-mejia-in-west-bengal', '2015-01-22 18:41:14', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(75, 8, 'Second Bhairav & Titas Railway Bridges, Bangladesh', '<p>\r\n	Bangladesh Railway is in the process of upgrading its existing Dhaka-Chittagong Corridor by providing double track for unhindered to and fro train services especially goods traffic. The assignment involves proposed construction of the 2 bridges over River Bhairav&amp;Titas along with completion of 2 sections of 6.25 km of railway track. The length of 2nd Bhairav Bridge and Titas bridges are 982m and 230m respectively. Double track between Bhairav Bazar &ndash; Ashuganj (4 km) and Akhaura Block hut &ndash; Akhaura Junction (2.25 km) will implement double tracking of Dhaka &ndash; Chittagong corridor.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Associated components of the assignment includes design of bridges, embankments, laying of MG Track with future conversion to BG, culverts, railway stations with buildings, platforms, railway yards, signalling and telecommunication.</p>', '14219323531.jpg', 'second-bhairav-and-titas-railway-bridges-bangladesh', '2015-01-22 18:42:33', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(76, 8, 'Kalinadi Bridge at Karwar on Konkan Railway', '<p>\r\n	This prestressed concrete bridge is 1400m long and is one of the major bridges on the Konkan Railway route.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The bridge has 42 spans supported by 30m long box girders resting on 2 nos.,1.5m diameter, twin circular piers and 4 nos., 1m diameter cast in situ piles.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	One of the special features of this project was the precasting of the full box in a single pour (125 cu m concrete). In addition, the box girders were completely precast and grouted in the casting yard and launched using an 80m long steel launching girder.</p>', '14219324430.jpg', 'kalinadi-bridge-at-karwar-on-konkan-railway', '2015-01-22 18:44:03', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(77, 8, 'Aroor Kumbalam Bridges, Kerala', '<p>\r\n	The bridge across Aroor has 29 spans each of 32.6m between centerlines of piers.The bridge across Nettoor- Kumbalam Backwater as well as the one across Nettoor-Champakara Backwater has only 4 spans. The details of all the spans are kept similar in order to minimise the cost. All spans have single box girders of a section 2.15m by 2.8m. The girders are matchcast in 7 segments in a precasting yard, transported by barges to the location, assembled on a supporting truss and epoxy interfaced before being prestressed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This is the first railway project where prestressed concrete bridges are constructed using the segmental construction method. The project has presented many interesting problems in casting the precast segments, transporting them on a pontoon, towing the pontoon to the bridge site, lifting the segments up by a gantry crane and assembling them in their final position.</p>', '14219325350.jpg', 'aroor-kumbalam-bridges-kerala', '2015-01-22 18:45:35', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(78, 8, 'Wheel and Axle Plant, Bangalore', '<p>\r\n	Plant for the Railways at Bangalore is one of the largest automated industrial plants in South Asia with an annual output of 70,000 wheels and 23,000 axles Area of 120 hectares with a floor area of 85,000 sqm Advanced design has minimized costs and energy utilization, yet achieved striking aesthetics Main wheel and axle shop is 51,500sqm with a roof constituted of 12m span precast folded plate shell elements resting on 30m span precast prestressed tied arch girders of 45 tons each</p>\r\n', '14219326092.jpg', 'wheel-and-axle-plant-bangalore', '2015-01-22 18:46:49', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(79, 8, 'Santragachi Railway Station', '<p>\r\n	Southeastern Railway with its headquarters in Kolkata has been using Howrah Station of the Eastern Railway, as terminus for its trains serving the south eastern areas of India. Howrah station is becoming very crowded due to the increase in the number of trains and SERly have been planning a terminus of its own. Since a Greenfield station is out of the question due to the land requirements, SE Rly have decided to develop Santragachi one of the way side stations in the South Eastern main line as a terminus.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The existing station has six platforms and a ticketing office. It has no road connections either. The developments will include a new station building (ground plus three floors) planned with concrete filled steel columns, parking areas for public and staff vehicles and two wheelers, road connections with nearby Kona Expressway at two levels, 6 km water line for supplying water to the new station from Shalimar, two new high level water tanks of 300,000 gallons with an underground tank of 1,000,000 gallons, escalators, improvements to platforms, passenger escalators, two 12 m wide foot over bridges with connections all platforms, The building would house all the offices for a terminal building. Two additional platforms are also likely to be included in the development.</p>', '14219326760.jpg', 'santragachi-railway-station', '2015-01-22 18:47:56', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(80, 7, 'Elevated Viaduct- 5.225kms.and Five Elevated Stations  Inderlok Mundka corridor of Delhi MRTS', '<p>\r\n	The Inderlok &ndash;Mundka corridor of Delhi MRTS is an elevated viaduct of length 5.225km with five elevated stations. There are as many as 148 spans of different lengths arranged all through the viaduct with the span length ranging from 16m to 37m. Also there is a 75m long continuous span placed over an existing railway track alongwith two side spans of length 62m.The superstructure system in the viaduct is of prescastprestressed type. The piers supporting the superstructures are either circular or elliptical and owning to the eccentricity of the centre line of alignment with the centre line of piers, the piers are categorized as concentric, cantilever and portal piers.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The five elevated stations are located at Inderlok, Ashok Park, Punjabi Bagh East, Shivaji Park and Madipur. At each station there are two floor levels, namely the Concourse level and the Platform level. The spans placed side by side to the platforms are RC cast &ndash;in-situ whereas the ones placed on either sides of the RC cast-in-situ spans are Precast.The columns supporting the structure are circular, rectangular or half elliptical. The foundation adopted is pile foundation type and piles used are either of diameters 0.8m or 1.2m</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Owner : Delhi Metro Rail Corporation</p>', '14219459733.jpg', 'elevated-viaduct-5-225kms-and-five-elevated-stations-inderlok-mundka-corridor-of-delhi-mrts', '2015-01-22 22:29:33', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(82, 7, 'Viaduct Portion of Stretch Adjacent to Sultanpur Station to QutabMinar', '<p class="STUPMetro">\r\n	The QutubMinar &ndash; Gurgaon corridor of Delhi MRTS has an elevated viaduct of length 0.883km near Sultanpur Station for supporting multiple tracks of Broad Gauge Coridor. There are as many as 32 spans of different lengths arranged all through the viaduct with the span length ranging from 16m to 24m.</p>\r\n<p class="STUPMetro">\r\n	The superstructure system in the viaduct is of precast girder with cast in situ slab. The girders are supported on portals and piers depending upon the location and number of tracks. The piers of superstructures are either circular or elliptical and owing to the eccentricity of the centre line of alignment with the centre line of piers, the piers are categorized as concentric, cantilever and portal piers. The type of foundation adopted in viaduct portion is pile foundation with pile diameter fixed to 1.0m.</p>\r\n<p class="STUPMetro">\r\n	Owner : Delhi Metro Rail Corporation</p>', '14219462190.jpg', 'viaduct-portion-of-stretch-adjacent-to-sultanpur-station-to-qutabminar', '2015-01-22 22:33:39', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(83, 7, 'Elevated Viaduct- 6.679kms and One Elevated Stations  Central Secretariat - Badarpur corridor of Delhi MRTS', '<p>\r\n	The Central Secretariat - Badarpur corridor of Delhi MRTS is an elevated viaduct of length 6.679km with one elevated station at SaritaVihar and Entry &amp; Exit connection to SaritaVihar Depot. There are as many as 188 spans of different lengths arranged all through the viaduct with the span length ranging from 19m to 37m.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The superstructure system in the viaduct is of prescastprestressed type and cast-in-situ prestressed types at depot. The piers supporting the superstructures are either circular or elliptical and owning to the eccentricity of the centre line of alignment with the centre line of piers, the piers are categorized as concentric, cantilever and portal piers. The maximum eccentricity is constrained to 2m for cantilever piers. The type of foundation adopted in viaduct portion is pile foundation (Bored cast-in-situ piles of diameter 1000) and open foundation.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The elevated station is located at SaritaVihar. At this station there are two floor levels, namely the Concourse level and the Platform level. The spans are RCC cast &ndash;in-situ. The columns supporting the structure are circular, rectangular or half elliptical. The foundation adopted is open foundation type.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Owner : Delhi Metro Rail Corporation</p>', '14219463080.679 km.jpg', 'elevated-viaduct-6-679kms-and-one-elevated-stations-central-secretariat-badarpur-corridor-of-delhi-mrts', '2015-01-22 22:35:08', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(84, 7, 'IGI Station Delhi Metro', '<p class="STUPMetro">\r\n	The IGI Airport Station &ndash; It is a 240m long and 36 m wide underground metro railway station building connecting the international airport at New Delhi. The building has total height of 16m constructed 2 m below ground level. There are two different working floors - platform level above base slab and concourse floor level above platform. The construction work proceeded from top. The two side walls of the station are constructed as diaphragm wall of 1m thickness which goes 26m below ground level leaving coupler bars in the wall at the appropriate locations for the construction of slabs. The successive levels of the slabs are constructed gradually from top by excavating downwards. Intermediate columns along transverse direction are constructed as piles at the time of construction of diaphragm wall and are built at later stage after completion of the casting of the slabs. Additional temporary piles in between permanent piles in longitudinal direction are constructed to carry the construction stage loading and are removed after the construction of base slab. The tunnel connecting the station building is about 2000m long and the top of tunnel from ground varies from 2m to 12m. At lower depth the tunnel is constructed as open cut and at higher depth top down method of construction is followed similar to the construction of station. Configuration of tunnels include single cell, double cell and triple cell box.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class="STUPMetro">\r\n	<o:p>&nbsp;</o:p>Owner : Delhi Metro Rail Corpoiation</p>\r\n<p class="STUPMetro">\r\n	<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n', '14219464013.jpg', 'igi-station-delhi-metro', '2015-01-22 22:36:41', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(85, 7, 'Elevated Viaduct and QutubMinar Elevated Station on Central Secretariat  QutubMinar corridor of Delhi MRTS', '<p>\r\n	The Central Secretariat &ndash; QutubMinar corridor of Delhi MRTS is an elevated viaduct of length 0.856km with elevated ramp of 40m length and one elevated stations (QutubMinar station). There are as many as 30 spans of different lengths arranged all through the viaduct with the span length ranging from 17m to 25m.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The superstructure system in the viaduct is of single track, double track and three track(Obligatory spans) cast in situ voided slab. The voided slabs are supported on portals. The piers of superstructures are either circular or elliptical. The type of foundation adopted in viaduct portion is pile foundation with pile diameter fixed to 1.0m.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The elevated stations QutubMinar station consist of Concourse level and the Platform level. The track is supported on beam &amp; slab arrangement The spans placed on both side of concourse level at platform level are RCC beam &amp; slab arrangement. The columns supporting the structure are circular, rectangular or half elliptical . The foundation adopted is open foundation.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Owner : Delhi Metro Rail Corporation</p>', '14219465224.jpg', 'elevated-viaduct-and-qutubminar-elevated-station-on-central-secretariat-qutubminar-corridor-of-delhi-mrts', '2015-01-22 22:38:42', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(86, 7, 'Design and Construction of Underground Section from Central Station to SubhasSarobar and Three Underground Stations', '<p>\r\n	There are three underground stations namely PhoolBagan Station, Sealdah Station and Central Station along with an underground cross over near Sealdah. The construction methodology as adopted for all the underground stations including Sealdah cross over is top down construction. Stations are generally 220m long and width is around 26m except for the Sealdah Station where width of the station is 44m. Either ends of all the stations are planned for launching / retrieving of Tunnel Boring Machine (TBM) and accordingly special construction design has been followed for these shafts. Diaphragm walls are being used for retaining the earth and steel plunge columns are used for the purpose of supporting roof and concourse slab during top down construction. Diaphragm walls and slabs are integrated with coupler joints.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Owner : Kolkata Metro Rail Corporation</p>', '14219466310.jpg', 'design-and-construction-of-underground-section-from-central-station-to-subhassarobar-and-three-underground-stations', '2015-01-22 22:40:31', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(87, 7, 'Elevated Viaduct Between Baiyappanahalli to MG Road in Reach R1', '<p>\r\n	This corridor is an elevated viaduct with a length of 6400m running between Baiyappanahalli station and MG Road station. There are 6 stations in this stretch namely Baiyappanahalli, Swamyvivekanantha, Indira Nagar, Ulsoor, Brigade road and MG Road stations. The main viaduct contains two tracks and having 209 piers. The obligatory junctions are at trinity circle and brigade road junctions. The alignment is straight and in curves where the alignment changes the direction.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The foundation for the majority of the piers in the viaduct is provided with 1200mm dia bored piles. For some of the piers near baiyyappanahalli where the hard strata is available at a shallow depth open type shallow foundations are provided. The piers are solid RCC Piers with elliptical shape. There are many normal piers accommodated on the median with pier protection. Cantilever and portal type piers are provided to support the superstructure where the alignment is deviating from median centre.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The superstructure for main two tracks consists of 25m/28m/31m standard spans with precast pre stressed box segments stressed together after launching in between end diaphragms. The segments are cast in casting yard and transported to site and launched using overhead launching girders. The obligatory spans are of cast in situ prestressed box girders. The obligatory span at brigade road and trinity circle are with 50m spans. The spans adjacent to stations are provided with non standard spans with I girders. The edges of superstructure deck slab are provided with precast parapets. Elastomeric type of bearings are provided for superstructure in standard spans and pot type bearings for obligatory spans. The expansion joints are provided at every pier location.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Owner : Bangalore Metro Rail Corporation</p>\r\n', '14219467490.jpg', 'elevated-viaduct-between-baiyappanahalli-to-mg-road-in-reach-r1', '2015-01-22 22:42:29', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(88, 7, 'Viaduct for Chennai Metro Rail Corporation, Chennai', '<p>\r\n	This corridor is with an elevated viaduct with a length of 4258m running between Koyambedu and vadapalani with 161 piers in the corridor. There are 4 stations in between the start and end of this project length namely Vadapalani, Arumbakkam, CMBT and Koyambedu stations. Nearer to koyambedu station, koyambedu depot and a shunting neck are located. The main viaduct contains two tracks, the entry to depot carries multi tracks and the shunting neck with one track. The alignment passes through koyambedu bus stand, and crosses NH &amp; SH roads.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The foundation for the entire length of viaduct is provided with 1200mm dia bored piles. The piers are solid RCC Piers. There are many normal piers accommodated on the median and few cantilever and portal type piers. The superstructure for main two tracks consists of 25m/28m/32m/34m spans with precast pre stressed box segments stressed together after launching in between end diaphragms. The segments are cast in casting yard and transported to site and launched. The multi track areas are provided with varying numbers and lengths of I girders from span to span. The shunting neck spans are provided with 2 nos of precast pre tensioned I girders. The edge of the superstructure deck slab are provided with precast parapets.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Owner: M/s. SOMA Enterprises Ltd</p>', '14219468582.jpg', 'viaduct-for-chennai-metro-rail-corporation-chennai', '2015-01-22 22:44:18', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(89, 7, 'Reach R3 Viaduct of Bangalore Metro Rail Project', '<p>\r\n	This corridor is with an elevated viaduct with a length of 6000m running between yeswanthpur station and and swastik station with 194 piers in the corridor. There are 6 stations in between the start and end of this project lengths namely Soap factory station , Mahalaxmi station, &nbsp;Rajaji Nagar station, Kuvempu road, Malleswaram station and swastika &nbsp;stations &nbsp;Nearer to mahalaxmi station a pocket track is located. The main viaduct contains two tracks, the entry to pocket track carries multi tracks. The alignment passes through Railway crossing at malleswarm, underpass at rajaji nagar and crosses SH roads.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The foundation for the majority of the piers in the viaduct is provided with 1200mm dia bored piles. For some of the piers near Iskcon where the hard strata is available at a shallow depth open type shallow foundations are provided. The piers are solid RCC Piers with circular ends. There are many normal piers accommodated on the median with pier protection. Few cantilever and portal type piers to support the superstructure where the alignment is deviating from median centre.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The superstructure for main two tracks consists of 25m/28m/32m/34m standard spans with precast pre stressed box segments stressed together after launching in between end diaphragms. The segments are cast in casting yard and transported to site and launched using overhead launching girders. The spans adjacent to stations are provided with non standard spans. The multi track areas are provided with varying numbers and lengths of I girders. &nbsp;The pocket track &nbsp;spans are provided with 2 nos of precast post tensioned I girders. The edges of superstructure deck slab are provided with precast parapets. Elastomeric type of bearings are provided for superstructure in normal stretches and pot type bearings are provided in cross over spans. The expansion joints are provided at every pier location except at cross overs where deck continuity is providesd at pier location to have a continuous deck as per track requirements.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The railway crossing at Malleswaram is provided with 135m curved span superstructure with 66m span. This span is being constructed by cast in place method of construction. &nbsp;</p>', '14219469791.jpg', 'reach-r3-viaduct-of-bangalore-metro-rail-project', '2015-01-22 22:46:19', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(90, 4, ' Rehabilitation and automation of 450 MLD Water Treatment Plant ', '<p>\r\n	The project involves rehabilitation and automation of the 450 MLD Water Treatment Plant located at Shahdara, Delhi. The plant was originally built in the 1980s to treat water from the Upper Ganga Canal and Yamuna river. &nbsp;STUP was also the original designer of this WTP. &nbsp;Rehabilitation work has involved replacement of all major electro-mechanical equipment, repair and rehabilitation of major civil structures, installation of instruments within the WTP and at inlet and outlet of all its reservoirs to measure quantity and quality of water supplied. &nbsp;The WTP residual recycle system consists of thickener, sludge drying beds and centrifuges.</p>\r\n', '14220700010.jpg', 'rehabilitation-and-automation-of-450-mld-water-treatment-plant', '2015-01-24 08:56:41', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(91, 4, 'Dwarka Water Supply Scheme', '<p>\r\n	The Rs. 7,500 million project has been constructed to supply water to the Dwarka sub-city in Delhi. &nbsp;It includes a 90 MGD intake to draw water from the Western Yamuna Canal; settling tanks; raw water sump and pump house; twin 1500mm diameter MS pipes of 2x23 km length, 50 MGD water treatment plant based on lamella plate clarifiers and rapid gravity filters, with a sludge recycle system, and clear water MS rising mains of 26km length, with diameters varying from 700 DN to 1600 DN. &nbsp;The raw water system and Water Treatment Plant operation is automated, and the two remote systems communicate with each other and the seven clear water reservoirs through GPRS system, with the Central Monitoring Station being located at the WTP.</p>\r\n', '14220702931.jpg', 'dwarka-water-supply-scheme', '2015-01-24 09:01:33', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(92, 4, 'Bengaluru Water Supply and Environmental Sanitation Master Plan ', '<p>\r\n	The project entailed preparing a Master Plan for water supply, sewerage and storm water drainage components for Bengaluru City for the project horizon of 2025. &nbsp;The project comprised studying the condition of the existing sewerage system, sewage pumping stations and sewage treatment plants and proposing new sewerage system for uncovered areas. &nbsp;The project area was 598 km2 &nbsp; covering a population of 65 lakhs. The total length of minor sewers is about 250 km and major sewers is about 200km. Rehabilitation measures were proposed for 90 km length of minor sewers. The existing sewage treatment plants including presently ongoing works are designed with a combined total capacity of about 500 MLD and an additional 250 MLD sewage treatment plants are required to handle the additional flow.</p>\r\n', '14220704450.jpg', 'bengaluru-water-supply-and-environmental-sanitation-master-plan', '2015-01-24 09:04:05', '2015-01-24 09:05:45', '1', '', '', '', 0),
(93, 4, '205 MLD STP at Kondli based on Activated Sludge Process and 363 MLD raw sewage pumping station', '<p>\r\n	The Sewage Treatment Plant has been designed to treat dilute sewage input from the adjoining drain in the initial stages and from the sewerage system when it is ready. &nbsp;The project components include raw sewage intake structure on the Gazipur Drain at Chilla Regulator with an approach bridge, pumping of raw sewage through rising mains of length about 4.0 km to the STP at Kondli and disposal of treated effluent into Hindon River through effluent channel (about 3.15km away). The plant will have automated operation and the gas generated is to be used for power production.</p>\r\n', '14220705130.jpg', '205-mld-stp-at-kondli-based-on-activated-sludge-process-and-363-mld-raw-sewage-pumping-station', '2015-01-24 09:05:13', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(94, 4, 'Kolkata Environmental Improvement Project, West Bengal ', '<p>\r\n	The objective of the project is to improve environmental conditions in the Kolkata Municipal Corporation (KMC) area, reduce poverty in low income areas through affordable basic urban services, community empowerment through participatory processes, protecting the environment from adverse developmental impacts. It also envisages improvements in urban services like sewerage, drainage including design of larger sewer pipes with rectangular box sections; betterment of canals and resettlement of canal bank dwellers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '14220706320.jpg', 'kolkata-environmental-improvement-project-west-bengal', '2015-01-24 09:07:12', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(95, 4, 'Chandrawal Project, Delhi', '<p>\r\n	The project objective is to achieve equitable and continuous water distribution in the National Capital Territory of Delhi by improving the water supply network including service network to customers thereby contributing to &nbsp;upgrading citizen&rsquo;s standards. &nbsp;The project, spanning nine years, and costing 34,310 million Yen, aims at rehabilitation, new construction and automation of 445 MLD WTP, UGRs and the distribution system in the command area of the Chandrawal WTP. &nbsp;The project is to be implemented in five packages: Package 1 &ndash; Chandrawal WTPs I &amp; II, Packages 2 to 4 &ndash; Transmission / Distribution Networks in 3 Zones, Package 5 - Strengthening of GIS Mapping.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '14220706990.jpg', 'chandrawal-project-delhi', '2015-01-24 09:08:19', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(96, 4, 'Multi Sector Project for Infrastructure Rehabilitation in Jammu & Kashmir ', '<p>\r\n	The project targets rehabilitation of existing infrastructure and utility facilities in the state. Jammu has a population of 1.26million. The water supply system suffers from poor pipe conditions and inequality in distribution. Supply varies from 25 to 300 litres per capita per day. Minimum supply is during winter, however the consumption being substantially higher during summer, water is scarce during summer also. Hence, the project aims to augment the system through creation of water sources and water intake, to improve sustainability and reduction in unaccounted for water.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '14220707480.jpg', 'multi-sector-project-for-infrastructure-rehabilitation-in-jammu-and-kashmir', '2015-01-24 09:09:08', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(97, 4, 'Water Supply for Northern Provincial Towns, LAOS PDR', '<p>\r\n	This project aimed at providing technical assistance to the Government to carry out a feasibility study and to prepare a project estimate for the construction of new water supply systems or for the rehabilitation and expansion of old systems in seven selected towns. The towns selected were - Phungsali, Houayxay, Xam-Nua, Xaignabouli, Pek, Phunhong and Pokxan. A feasibility study for water supply development for each of the towns was carried out, which included physical, institutional, financial, economic and social aspects. Field surveys were also carried out to supplement this information.</p>\r\n', '14220708310.jpg', 'water-supply-for-northern-provincial-towns-laos-pdr', '2015-01-24 09:10:32', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(98, 4, 'Sewage Treatment Plant at Lansab, Muscat', '<p>\r\n	This sewage treatment plant is designed as an activated sludge plant with an extended aeration process. The process flow for the treated quality of effluent is designed as per British Standards, so as to satisfy the stringent requirements of the Ministry of Environment and Water Resources, Sultanate of Oman. The large quantity of good quality effluent water, thus made available, is used for irrigating plants and trees through a drip system. The plant which is constructed as a RCC inter-connected structure above ground level, consists of an aeration tank, a settling tank, a balancing tank, a sludge tank, a chlorine contact tank and an effluent tank along with a plant room housing raw sewage pumps, air blowers, sludge return pumps, a chlorine dosing pump, multimedia pressure filters, filter feed pumps, irrigation /backwash pumps and control panels.</p>\r\n', '14220709130.jpg', 'sewage-treatment-plant-at-lansab-muscat', '2015-01-24 09:11:53', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(99, 4, 'Delhi Pipeline Project', '<p>\r\n	To meet the increasing water demand of New Delhi, a raw water treatment plant of 270 cusec (660 MLD) capacity was envisaged at Sonia Vihar near the banks of Yamuna River. The mode of conveyance is a pipeline flowing &lsquo;by gravity&rsquo;. This 35km long conveyance system consists of a prestressed concrete pipeline, siphons and viaducts. The pipeline lies either below ground level as a conduit, buried from nil to 7m depth, or runs across natural depressions as a viaduct. The alignment also required the pipeline to be siphoned at road crossings, under railway track, drains and minor distributaries. The main length of pipeline is 21,000m. The total viaduct length is 7,200m and that of siphons is 4,800m.</p>\r\n', '14220709880.jpg', 'delhi-pipeline-project', '2015-01-24 09:13:08', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0);
