(100, 4, '130 MLD Water Supply Scheme for Left Bank of River Chambal for Kota City ', '<p>\r\n	(National Capital Region Water Supply Augmentation Scheme) (NCRPB/KFW Germany funding)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The project consists of following main components:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	(i)<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Design of Intake Well at river Chambal (200 MLD)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	(ii)<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Design of 130 MLD WTP &amp; Clear Water Reservoir and Pumping Station</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	(iii)<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Design and Modelling of Transmission up to OHSR (60 Km), MS/DI (Dia. 350-1400 mm)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	(iv)<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Design of New OHSR (8 Nos.) and Peripheral Mains</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	(v)<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Remodeling of existing peripheral mains and OHSRs</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	(vi)<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Construction Supervision &amp; Quality Control</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	(vii)<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Project Management and Bid Process Management</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	(viii)<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Design of Distribution Network (180 km)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	(ix)<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Rehabilitation of existing OHSR, Booster Pump Stations &ndash; 2 Nos.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	(x)<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>O&amp;M for a period of 10 Yrs.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	(xi)<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Service population covered &ndash; 8.67 Lakhs</p>', '14220710650.jpg', '130-mld-water-supply-scheme-for-left-bank-of-river-chambal-for-kota-city', '2015-01-24 09:14:25', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(101, 9, 'Fourth Oil Berth at Butcher Island, Mumbai', '<p>\r\n	The 4th oil berth in Mumbai harbour caters to oil tankers berthing in deep waters. The project comprises an approach bund 547m long, an approach jetty 5.9m wide &amp; 1248m long and berthing and mooring facilities for vessels upto 1,50,000 DWT. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	An interesting feature of the project is its optimal design concept which catered economically to the strong waves and high berthing forces and at the same time met the tight construction schedule fixed for the project. The design concept takes into account the difficult and hazardous conditions of working in the sea and utilised fully the potential of on-shore precasting and transportation by sea.</p>', '14220712551.jpg', 'fourth-oil-berth-at-butcher-island-mumbai', '2015-01-24 09:17:35', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(102, 9, 'Grain Storage Facility at Jebel Ali Port, Dubai, UAE', '<p>\r\n	The fully mechanised grain unloading, handling and storage complex at Jebel Ali Port, is designed to handle six different kinds of grains. It has facilities for unloading grain from bulk carrier ships of upto 80,000t capacity and 12 prestressed vertical silos, each with a capacity of 10,000t for the storage of grain. &nbsp;The project consisted of detailed design of civil engineering elements, a loading/ unloading system, conveyor system, elevator tower, junction towers and forklift equipments.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This facility was built rapidly with each silo being complete d in 14 days and the entire complex concluded in 24 months.&nbsp;</p>', '14220713470.jpg', 'grain-storage-facility-at-jebel-ali-port-dubai-uae', '2015-01-24 09:19:07', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(103, 9, 'Eighth Cargo Berth at Kandla Port, Gulf of Kutchh, Gujarat', '<p>\r\n	With the increase in the quantity of cargo at Kandla Port in the Gulf of Kutchh, it was decided to construct the eighth cargo berth. This is part of the expansion plan of Kandla Port and is to be constructed in continuation with the existing seventh cargo berth. It is designed to handle 4,00,000t per annum of cargo and can handle ships upto 45,000 DWT. The salient features of this project include the construction of a cargo berth 208.74m long &amp; 55.26m wide and a quay and transit area comprising RCC precast as well as an in-situ superstructure which is supported on deep piles complete with fenders, bollards etc. Ground treatment with band drains and preloading, in an area 208.74m long by 149.74m wide including instrumentation, is to be used as a container stack yard.</p>\r\n', '14220714440.jpg', 'eighth-cargo-berth-at-kandla-port-gulf-of-kutchh-gujarat', '2015-01-24 09:20:44', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(104, 9, 'Multipurpose Berths at Vishakhapatnam Port, Vizag', '<p>\r\n	Vizag Sea Port Ltd. is to set up two multipurpose berths, each 255m long, with required material handling and storage facilities of &nbsp;over 90,000 sqm at Visakhapatnam Port on BOT basis. The berth is to handle ships upto 80000 DWT for import/export of dry bulk cargo upto 9.0 million t per annum.</p>\r\n', '14220714900.jpg', 'multipurpose-berths-at-vishakhapatnam-port-vizag', '2015-01-24 09:21:30', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(105, 9, 'Shiplift-cum-Dry Dock, Surat, Gujarat', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;">\r\n	This is the first shiplifting platform in India with a dry dock/ wet basin facility. The lifting is done by twenty, 100t hydraulic jacks controlled by a computerized synchronizing system which prevents differential lifting of more than 5 mm. The shiplift caters to ships upto 120m length and 2000 DWT.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n', '14220715390.jpg', 'shiplift-cum-dry-dock-surat-gujarat', '2015-01-24 09:22:19', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(106, 9, 'Virtual Jetty for IOCL, KandlaPort , Gulf of Kutchh, Gujarat', '<p>\r\n	This virtual jetty is situated beside the proposed liquid cargo jetty of IFFCO and is designed to handle petroleum products upto 25,00,000t per annum and can handle ships upto 30,000 DWT. The project consists of the construction of an approach bridge with a steel superstructure from the shore carrying a steel piperack structure and a walkway founded on steel liner encased concrete cast-in-situ deep piles. A steel truss bridge carries pipelines with a walkway connecting an approach bridge and cradle pontoon. There is also a gangway steel bridge carrying a pipeline and a walkway connecting a cradle and a main pontoon, and four mooring buoys complete with anchors, chains, bollards, fenders and other deck fittings etc., pipelines carrying class &lsquo;B&rsquo; petroleum products upto IOCL&rsquo;s old dock line and allied civil works including construction of pipeline pedestals.</p>\r\n', '14220716260.jpg', 'virtual-jetty-for-iocl-kandlaport-gulf-of-kutchh-gujarat', '2015-01-24 09:23:46', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(107, 9, 'Offshore Fabrication Yard at Jellingham', '<p>\r\n	A fabrication yard, for the supply of jackets and other structures to ONGC, has been constructed at Jellingham, 16km downstream of Haldia along the Hooghly river. The jackets will be upto 4,000t in weight and 300m in length and will be fabricated on skid beams fixed on precast RCC sleepers. Cellular bulkheads which are 600m long (cell diameter 15.28m) consisting of straight web sheet piles 22m long, are constructed as quay walls for berthing. Geotextile (spun blended polypropylene fabric) has been used as a reinforcing material with 0.8m boulder filling on top to improve the safe bearing capacity of the soil. The main components of the project include an administrative building, welding workshop, generator house, precast RCC sleeper blocks, overhead tank, cellular sheet pile bulk head construction, fendering system for berthing, officers&rsquo; camp and labour camp.</p>\r\n', '14220717020.jpg', 'offshore-fabrication-yard-at-jellingham', '2015-01-24 09:25:02', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(108, 9, 'Liquid Cargo Jetty for IFFCO at Kandla Port, Gujarat', '<p>\r\n	To meet the increasing demand of handling imported items, IFFCO built their own liquid cargo jetty in front of the plant. The handling capacity of the liquid cargo jetty is 20,00,000t per annum. The project included construction of a jetty designed for berthing ships upto 45000 DWT, an approach bridge to the jetty, four mooring dolphins, steel walkway bridges connecting the mooring dolphins with the jetty, a connecting bridge between IFFCO and the 3rd oil jetty of KPT, an offshore pump house, a pipeline manifold platform, illumination of the jetty and approach bridge area.</p>\r\n', '14220718150.jpg', 'liquid-cargo-jetty-for-iffco-at-kandla-port-gujarat', '2015-01-24 09:26:55', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(109, 9, 'Land Based Drilling Platform at Hazira', '<p>\r\n	The project comprises of a platform about 80 m x 80 m in the sea for installation of natural gas wells and an approach of about 1.5 km length, connecting the drilling platform with the shore. The sea water depth at the platform location is about 8.0 m. The approach is a rock mound structure with armour stones on the side slopes. The sides of the platform are rubble peripheral embankments with sand filling inside. For protection of outer slopes, in addition to rubble protection, dolos each weighting about 5 t are provided.</p>\r\n', '14220720120.jpg', 'land-based-drilling-platform-at-hazira', '2015-01-24 09:30:12', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(110, 9, 'Third Oil Jetty at Kandla Port, Kachh, Gujarat', '<p>\r\n	The third oil jetty at Kandla Port has a handling capacity of 20,00,000t per annum. It is being used for traffic in POL and other liquid bulk cargo passing through Kandla Port. The jetty consists of a pile- supported platform with a RCC precast superstructure. It is designed for berthing ships upto 45000 DWT. Four mooring dolphins, approach bridge and pipeline manifold platforms are also provided.</p>\r\n', '14220720840.jpg', 'third-oil-jetty-at-kandla-port-kachh-gujarat', '2015-01-24 09:31:24', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(111, 11, 'Airoli Bridge across Thane Creek', '<p>\r\n	This new bridge across Thane Creek has 2 parallel decks with an aggregate length of 2.22km.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The technology successfully used for the construction of the Thane Creek Bridge foundations was reused in this bridge. The superstructure has precast simply supported spans of 50m which were transported by a floating mechanical derrick and placed in position.</p>', '14220725440.jpg', 'airoli-bridge-across-thane-creek', '2015-01-24 09:39:04', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(112, 11, 'Bhima Aqueduct, Maharashtra', '<p>\r\n	The Bhima aqueduct was constructed by the Government of Maharashtra to irrigate drought prone areas of Sholapur district. The aqueduct, with a discharge of 42.5 cumecs, is 947m in length with a 3.5m roadway and continuous spans of 41.5m. The aqueduct is supported on 23 tall, slender, hollow circular piers 40m high, constructed with climbing forms. The truncated circular cross section which is 4.8m in diameter achieves high hydraulic and structural efficiency and reduces transverse effects, &nbsp;due to membrane forces, easily taken by transverse prestressing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Rapid and economic construction was achieved by adopting the free cantilever method, using precast match cast epoxy glued prestressed segments, which was the latest technology at that time. It is an outstanding structure in many ways and is a major shift from traditional methods of design and construction of aqueducts. It combines aesthetics with efficiency and economy. Specially designed and fabricated lightweight equipment for construction were fabricated locally.</p>', '14220726360.jpg', 'bhima-aqueduct-maharashtra-19', '2015-01-24 09:40:36', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(113, 11, 'Bhosari Flyover on Pune Nashik Road', '<p>\r\n	Total Length of Flyover is 1535 Mtr. including solid approaches on both end and super structure is precast segmental Box Girder Type. Top width of Box Girder is 19.5 Mtr. (4 Lane with 1.2 Mtr. Median).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Superstructure is resting on single pier span of 40 Mtr. Length. Reinforcement Earth Work for approaches at both ends has been provided..</p>', '14220726830.jpg', 'bhosari-flyover-on-pune-nashik-road', '2015-01-24 09:41:23', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(114, 11, 'Eastern Freeway Section from Panjarpole to Chembur Mankhurd Link road ', '<p>\r\n	Mumbai Urban Infrastructure project (MUIP), Eastern Freeway is one of the projects of Vital Metropolitan importance in improving vehicular mobility.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Eastern Freeway is divided in three sections i.e. (a) From Museum to Anik (b) Anik to Panjarpole &amp; (c) Panjarpole to Chembur Mankhurd Link Road.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The section of Eastern freeway covered by this contract is from Panjarpole to Chembur Mankhurd Link Road Km 0/000 to 2/500. The total length of this link is 2.5 km as per original scope of work. &nbsp;This starts from Shivaji Chowk &nbsp;at second level at 22 m from the existing road. &nbsp;At his point, above the existing road the Metro Rail crosses at the first level. Alignment passes through Panjarpole junction along Waman Tukaram Patil marg up to Borba Devi Chowk and after crossing Govandi ROB it crosses CMLR road to reach Indian Oil Nagar.</p>', '14220727410.jpg', 'eastern-freeway-section-from-panjarpole-to-chembur-mankhurd-link-road', '2015-01-24 09:42:21', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(115, 11, 'Elevated Road from Western Express Highway to International Airport,', '<p>\r\n	The Sahar Elevated Access Road is an elevated road under construction in Mumbai. It provides direct connectivity between the Western Express Highway (WEH) and the forecourts of Terminal T2 of the Chhatrapati Shivaji International Airport. The 3.3 Km long access road has 4 entry points and 2 exit points. The road includes an underpass for vehicles and pedestrians on the WEH, a tunnel and ramps connecting the highway to the terminal, bypassing the congested roadways below.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The corridor begins at the WEH heading east at grade until the elevated section takes it over the Sahar Road. The corridor continues east over the Indian Airlines Project Road until it reaches the current main approach road of the International terminal where the corridor disperses into ramps leading to the arrival and departure forecourts.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The elevated road consists of 30 spans of 35 metre long (115 ft) precast concrete segments erected using a specially fabricated launching girder and strand jack. The pillars measure 2.5 by 2.8 meters (8.2 ft x 9.2 ft) at the base. The 27.6 metre (91 ft) deck superstructure is composed of a 9 metre wide (30 ft) precast central spine and two 9.3 metre (31 ft) cantilever wings on either side connected to the central spine by concrete stitching and transverse pre-stressing methods.&nbsp;</p>', '14220728570.jpg', 'elevated-road-from-western-express-highway-to-international-airport', '2015-01-24 09:44:17', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(116, 11, 'Railway Bridge over Vasai Creek, Maharashtra', '<p>\r\n	This bridge is 4km long with spans of 48.5m, each weighing 750 t.They are precast, shifted &amp; launched into position using entirely hand operated equipment and a simple barge. This was among the first examples of such large precast spans being used to construct a bridge for the Indian Railways.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Since the earlier bridge had corroded, special precautions have been taken in constructing the new bridge. Entire spans were totally precast on the shore, to achieve very high quality of construction.Thereafter the spans were lifted on to a specially designed barge by using the rising tide, were towed 3.5km to site and lowered in position using the falling tide.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The construction equipment engineered for the bridge was economical and suitable for use by a developing country contractor.</p>', '14220729250.jpg', 'railway-bridge-over-vasai-creek-maharashtra-72', '2015-01-24 09:45:25', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(117, 11, 'Wheel and Axle Plant, Bangalore', '<p>\r\n	Plant for the Railways at Bangalore is one of the largest automated industrial plants in South Asia with an annual output of 70,000 wheels and 23,000 axles Area of 120 hectares with a floor area of 85,000 sqm Advanced design has minimized costs and energy utilization, yet achieved striking aesthetics Main wheel and axle shop is 51,500sqm with a roof constituted of 12m span precast folded plate shell elements resting on 30m span precast prestressed tied arch girders of 45 tons each</p>\r\n', '14220729810.jpg', 'wheel-and-axle-plant-bangalore-78', '2015-01-24 09:46:21', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(118, 11, 'Sindhudurg Airport, Maharashtra', '<p>\r\n	The &nbsp;innovations &nbsp;include &nbsp;a &nbsp;component-based &nbsp; flexible floor plate which can respond to the changing &nbsp;business plans of the developer &nbsp;and the airline industry, and an Airport Village which provides a comfortable &nbsp;shaded atmosphere for the visitors to this facility. The passenger terminal building will have an area of 9250 sqm and a peak hour capacity of 200 departing and 200 arriving passengers. The scope includes consultancy work for Master Planning, Detailed Project Report, Detailed Design of the Passenger Terminal Building, ATC and Technical building and all other buildings, Airside and Landside works, Infrastructure, Airfield Ground Lighting etc as well as the business plan and techno feasibility study for this PPP airport. STUP is entrusted with design and comprehensive project management services for the entire airport development of this Greenfield international airport.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	A signature feature of this airport is the flowing roof and the coconut palm skylight, which defines the ambience this unique airport located in sylavan coastal surroundingsin the lush green Konkan belt of India.</p>', '14220730510.jpg', 'sindhudurg-airport-maharashtra', '2015-01-24 09:47:31', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(119, 11, 'Patni Computers, Chennai ', '<p>\r\n	The project houses software units, training facilities customer care centres, and staff elfare facilities for one of India&rsquo;s leading software giants. This project is specially designed to meet high benchmarks of rapid construction, high efficiency and flexibility and reusability of spaces. A unique and innovative double cantilever structural system was innovated to meet the demanding timeframe of 9 months Design to Delivery requested by the clients. An expressive Palm tree inspired skyframe from the signature element of this design ,crowning the roof of this building while simultaneously housing a cafeteria and recreational spaces with its inspirational cover. This roof is inspired by an expressive functional architecture, an aesthetic reminiscent of British hightech architecture and is inspired by the Palm trees of the surrounding coastal region. Specially designed light wells bring indirect light to the interior spaces. The building is designed with a solar screen roof for reduced heat gain and naturally ventilated public spaces in an effort to make a sustainable and futuristic environment for the clients.</p>\r\n', '14220732680.jpg', 'patni-computers-chennai', '2015-01-24 09:51:08', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(120, 11, 'IIMC Complex at Joka, Kolkata', '<p>\r\n	Indian Institute of Management had its first campus opened in 1961 at Joka in the Southern suburb of Kolkata. Over the last fifty years it has produced an impressive list of alumni representing the Corporate and Intellectual echelon of India. Kolkata branch of STUP has had an opportunity to stay in close touch with their ongoing infrastructure expansion projects undertaken in phases since 2007. The responsibilities of STUP include Project Management including Contract Administration, Quality Control, Progress Monitoring, Certification of Bills etc. The present expansion project handled by STUP has covered Construction of Management Development Center, Teaching Complex for Post Graduate and Doctoral Program, New Hostel Blocks for Post Graduate Program, Family type dwelling accommodation, Refurbishing of existing Buildings, Renovation of Interior of all buildings, Development of new Roads and adjoining Land etc.</p>\r\n', '14220733660.jpg', 'iimc-complex-at-joka-kolkata', '2015-01-24 09:52:46', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(121, 12, 'Bridge across River Sharavati on NH17, Honnavar, Karnataka', '<p>\r\n	The Sharavati bridge, located in an aggressive coastal environment, has 34 spans &amp; a total length of 1067m. The bridge was completed in 1971 but started showing distress in the longitudinal and cross prestressing wires, passive reinforcement and bearing, due to corrosion, spalling and deterioration of concrete by carbonation and penetration of chlorides.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The bridge was closed to commercial traffic. A comprehensive program of in-situ and laboratory testing was carried out. A scheme of emergency repairs to enable the bridge to be opened to commercial traffic as well as a detailed scheme of repairs was proposed.</p>', '14220735630.jpg', 'bridge-across-river-sharavati-on-nh17-honnavar-karnataka', '2015-01-24 09:56:03', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(122, 12, 'Times of India Building, Mumbai', '<p>\r\n	The Times of India Building, a heritage structure constructed in 1901, has been exposed to the aggressive marine environment of Mumbai for decades. Over this period of nearly a century, many structural and architectural modifications were carried out.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The work included evaluating the effect of renovations, additions and modifications to assess the present structural safety of the building, to prepare a rehabilitation scheme and to evaluate the expectations regarding the future use of this building. A rehabilitation scheme was prepared based on the results of testing, investigation and structural analysis.</p>', '14220736110.jpg', 'times-of-india-building-mumbai', '2015-01-24 09:56:51', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(123, 12, 'Rehabilitation in cyclone affected areas of Jagatsinghpur Dist., Orissa', '<p>\r\n	The cyclone in October 1999 caused widespread damage and loss of life in Orissa. The Government of Maharashtra has taken up rehabilitation work in the coastal state.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The work includes construction supervision and project management of:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	1. 100 school buildings cum cyclone shelters</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	2. 700 houses</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	3. 23 Colleges (Repair &amp; Rehabilitation)</p>', '14220737650.jpg', 'rehabilitation-in-cyclone-affected-areas-of-jagatsinghpur-dist-orissa', '2015-01-24 09:59:25', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(124, 12, 'Eleven Villages in Latur and Osmanabad District, Maharashtra', '<p>\r\n	The earthquake of 1993 measuring 6.5 on the Richter scale caused widespread devastation and loss of life in the district of Latur and Osmanabad in Maharashtra State. The Government of India obtained a loan/ credit from International Bank of Reconstruction and Development (IBRD) and International Development Agency (IDA), has allocated a portion of it to complete relocation and rehabilitation of 11 severely devastated villages. The work includes construction of 2000 new houses, 16 community centers and school building.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	An interesting feature of this work is that community participation of the villagers is encouraged at the planning and preliminary design stage.</p>\r\n', '14220738250.jpg', 'eleven-villages-in-latur-and-osmanabad-district-maharashtra', '2015-01-24 10:00:25', '2015-01-27 10:51:15', '1', '', '', '', 0),
(125, 12, 'Rehabilitation of Cooling Tower at Dhuvaran Thermal Power Station, Baroda', '<p>\r\n	Between 1970 &amp; 1972, two Natural Draught Cooling Towers (units 5 &amp; 6) were constructed at Dhuvaran Thermal Power Station. A portion of cooling tower no. 6 fell down in 1993, destroying the peripheral channel and partly the fill structure.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The inspection and testing of these towers showed extensive cracking of shell, deep penetration of carbonation, low resistivity of concrete and a severe corrosion of steel. The repair and rehabilitation measures included dismantling the shell of cooling tower no. 6 upto the neck, painting the shell to stop chloride penetration, repair of cracks, casting a new shell around the existing one and provision of external prestressing for shells as a short term strengthening measure.</p>', '14220740450.jpg', 'rehabilitation-of-cooling-tower-at-dhuvaran-thermal-power-station-baroda', '2015-01-24 10:04:05', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(126, 12, 'Mahatma Gandhi Setu across Ganga at Patna', '<p>\r\n	On investigating this bridge the immediate distress shows hammering at the hinges on passage of vehicles, finger type expansion joints in an advanced state of distress, wearing coat cracks, spalling of concrete at transverse joints, longitudinal cracks in precast segments at 700 to 800mm from web face, leakage of water inside the box girder from joints between segments and from holes provided for lifting the segments, honeycombing of concrete on the soffits of girders and level difference between two cantilever arms at the middle of some spans.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The investigation and testing is in progress. It is anticipated that the rehabilitation scheme will involve external prestressing to make up the loss due to relaxation, replacement of expansion joints, repairs / replacement of hinges and replacement of parapet sections lost due to accidents.</p>', '14220741160.jpg', 'mahatma-gandhi-setu-across-ganga-at-patna', '2015-01-24 10:05:16', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(127, 12, 'Dam Safety Assurance and Rehabilitation Project Orissa', '<p>\r\n	Remedial measures have been formulated for the rehabilitation of ten large dams in order to enhance their safety status in this World Bank Aided project. The formulation of remedial measures is based on state-of-the-art technology and has resulted in the evolution of a design standard.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The height of the dams vary from 12m to 28m comprising earth dams with concrete and/or masonry spillways with or without gates and weirs with pervious and impervious foundations. The project includes assessment of safety of existing structures through appropriate site investigations &amp; laboratory studies.</p>', '14220741970.jpg', 'dam-safety-assurance-and-rehabilitation-project-orissa', '2015-01-24 10:06:37', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(128, 12, 'Bridge across River Zuari near Borim, Goa', '<p>\r\n	This bridge located in an aggressive coastal environment is 410m long, including four viaduct spans and has prestressed concrete box girders with cantilever arms and suspended spans. The bridge has RCC cellular piers.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The initially apparent distress includes a substantial deflection of the structure observed at the hinge location, loud grating noises when vehicles traverse this point and deterioration of the finger type expansion joints. It is felt that the distresses observed are due to excessive deflection caused by relaxation losses in the prestress and due to improper functioning of the piston of the hinge. The rehabilitation scheme is expected to consist of application of external prestress, replacement of the hinge, and the normal surface repairs expected after more than a decade of service in the aggressive environment.</p>', '14220742630.jpg', 'bridge-across-river-zuari-near-borim-goa', '2015-01-24 10:07:43', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(129, 12, 'Reconstruction of Damaged Jetty, Trincomalee, Sri Lanka', '<p>\r\n	M/s. TCCL, a leading cement manufacturing company constructed an exclusive berth for importing raw materials. In the recent past, one of the main dolphins and the hopper pad suffered extensive damage. This created a serious impediment to the normal functioning of the port facilities and support systems. The project involved reconstruction of the damaged main berthing dolphins and the hopper pad.</p>\r\n', '14220743300.jpg', 'reconstruction-of-damaged-jetty-trincomalee-sri-lanka', '2015-01-24 10:08:50', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(130, 12, 'First Road Bridge across Thane Creek, Mumbai', '<p>\r\n	The first road bridge across Thane Creek is a 1,836m long, 39 span, pre-stressed concrete structure connecting the mainland with Mumbai&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The structure is located in a severely aggressive environment, resulting in corrosion of cables and severe cracking of concrete&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The recommendations included the development and design of a special movable suspended platform for inspection and maintenance, application of epoxy paint and external pre-stressing to girders</p>', '14220743980.jpg', 'first-road-bridge-across-thane-creek-mumbai', '2015-01-24 10:09:58', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(133, 2, 'DOHACITY MASTERPLAN, 2008 ', '<p>\r\n	Conceived jointly under the aegis of a team of international architects and planners (NORPLAN/ASPLAN/ NSW with Stup),&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Doha is designed as a sustainable city, its urban fabric defined by a green web, and a fertile green crescent, where , along the corniche, the Old city, the New Institutional City , and the Manhattan like West Bay development will coexist, displaying the difference and chaotic diversity that defines contemporary cities.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The defining aspect of this design however is the fabric of the city itself. A palimpsest, it overlays on the structure of the existing automobile city - a series of layered networks. The Blue Layer responds to the presence of a high water table by dredging an Array of Oases, networked by wadis and waterways, its lace-like character resembling the Arabesque. This creates a series of waterfronts within the structure of the city, a modern day Venice, for the word Qatar itself is derived from catarrh , which means the constant search for water.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Green Layer demarcates the self sustaining communities. Designed as a green web, it forms a transition from the central park to the fabric of the city and the desert beyond. The narrow green fingers, articulating shaded public spaces, souks and streets, surrounded by houses and community buildings- its scale and narrow linear character responsive to climate and its Islamic context, while simultaneously infusing life into the community spaces. Each web enclosure is scaled for pedestrian travel and trams, encouraging public transport and placing amenities in 10 minute walking distances.</p>', '14220749520.jpg', 'dohacity-masterplan-2008', '2015-01-24 10:19:12', '2015-01-29 17:09:30', '1', '', '', '', 9),
(134, 2, 'Tata Consultancy Services Corporate Park & Training Centre ', '<p>\r\n	This integrated campus integrating production centres, public amenities, training facilities as well into a single habitat in Trivandrum is designed as a dynamic but contextual architectural landmark for India&rsquo;s leading IT solutions company. The architecture combines the concerns for creating a green environment, while aspiring to create covered circulation spines, complete segregation of pedestrian and vehicular traffic, optimized orientation with respect to solar and wind movements and the use of traditional architectural elements and craftsmanship while creating a contemporary architectural solution.</p>\r\n', '14220749990.jpg', 'tata-consultancy-services-corporate-park-and-training-centre', '2015-01-24 10:19:59', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(135, 2, 'Airtel Corporate Office and Training Centre, Chandigarh 0', '<p>\r\n	This building has been designed as an iconic building inspired by the sleek sinuous aero- dynamic futuristic forms which represent the emerging culture of this vibrant company. The building orients itself according to the climate and is designed as strips with glazed facades corresponding to the solar movements and the sloping eastern facade reduces solar insolation. The unique feature of the building is its open character, with a streetscape shape, forming a green spine, bringing the employees and staff together. The building was designed to create a prominent mind space for Airtel in Chandigarh as to inspire its employees to meet the challenges of the future in a conducive environment.</p>\r\n', '14220750690.jpg', 'airtel-corporate-office-and-training-centre-chandigarh-0', '2015-01-24 10:21:09', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(136, 2, 'Club Mahindra, Resorts Coorg ', '<p>\r\n	The Club Mahindra Resorts project at Coorg is inspired by the local character of coffee plantation houses. An innovative tree house colony is the highlight of this design.. A blend of contemporary architecture and local materials and forms the central theme of this complex. The room plans have been designed to maximize openness while simultaneously allowing flexibility of use. Resort like feel have been achieved through the cottage clusters in various combinations. The spiraling tree houses and the island pool are the most significant features of the Resort. This is a green eco friendly resort using natural ventilation and local materials and craftsmanship.</p>\r\n', '14220751341.jpg', 'club-mahindra-resorts-coorg', '2015-01-24 10:22:14', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(137, 2, 'Indian Institute of Science & Technology, Trivandrum ', '<p>\r\n	This project has been designed as a pioneering Institute for Space, Science &amp; Technology situated in most difficult terrain between steep valleys and ridges in a dense forest. The architecture while expressing contemporary character seeks to draw inspiration from the rich traditional architectural context of the region. The sloping roofs are designed innovatively to symbolize flight and buildings are designed to take full advantage of the topography. A great value has been put on the connectivity between the residential and academic campus, ensuring that all the facilities are accessible by by-cycle and pedestrians. The design is environment friendly maximizing the use of cross ventilation and minimizing the use of glass and air conditioners. The campus houses a large central library, convention centre, administrative buildings as well as the various academic institutions, as well as recreational facilities for this prestigious institution.</p>\r\n', '14220752160.jpg', 'indian-institute-of-science-and-technology-trivandrum', '2015-01-24 10:23:36', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(138, 2, 'Logistics SEZ in Navi Mumbai ', '<p>\r\n	India&rsquo;s first wholly integrated logistics SEZ houses state of the art corporate buildings, warehousing facilities as well as sustainably designed welfare facilities. The corporate building with its active sun breaker facades as well as the cafetteria and welfare complex with its sweeping green roof are some of the unique aspects of this project.</p>\r\n', '14220753140.jpg', 'logistics-sez-in-navi-mumbai', '2015-01-24 10:25:14', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(139, 2, 'Indoor Velodrome for the Commonwealth Games, 2010, New Delhi ', '<p>\r\n	State of the Art Velodrome is one of the defining structures of the Commonwealth Games 2010.Using two largespan bow- arches to suspeend the roof shell STUP has executed a daring and flamboyant design for this prestigious structure housing one of the best velodrome tracks in the world.</p>\r\n', '14220754350.jpg', 'indoor-velodrome-for-the-commonwealth-games-2010-new-delhi', '2015-01-24 10:27:15', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0),
(140, 2, 'Kirloskar Toyoda Textile Machinery Manufacturing Unit, Bangalore', '<p>\r\n	The factory consists of four major units: the machine shop, the administrative building, the canteen, and the services building. Lightweight north light steel roof trusses have been used for the economical, yet rapid and easy construction of these elegant and colourfully painted buildings.</p>\r\n', '14220754870.jpg', 'kirloskar-toyoda-textile-machinery-manufacturing-unit-bangalore', '2015-01-24 10:28:07', NULL, '1', '', '', '', 0);
