(3, 'Energy, Telecommunication and Space Infrastructure', '<p>\r\n	The Energy, Telecommunication and Space Infrastructure Group at STUP Consultants Pvt. Ltd. &nbsp;is involved mainly in the design &nbsp;of structures related to power plants. In the early 60s the group started its operation in the country with nuclear power related structures. Since then it has rendered a wide range of services in a number of other power projects especially in the following areas.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;"> </span>Containments for nuclear reactor buildings</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Thermal and hydro-electric power projects</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Thermal and structural design of natural and induced draft cooling towers</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Functional and structural design of tall chimneys</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Cryogenic tanks for storage of LNG</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Pylons for boilers</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Communication towers</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Satellite launching stations</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Turbine and boiler houses</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Material handling systems</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Group has excellent analytical capabilities for carrying out static, dynamic as well as non-linear analysis of structures. It is equipped with state-of-the-art finite elements softwares.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	These unique structures were distinguished by the utilization of well-adapted new technologies paying particular attention to the use of local resources, effecting substantial savings in cost and high functional and aesthetic values. One of the basic factors that contributed towards the success of these projects was the deep involvement of STUP Consultants and its determination to stand by them from inception to completion. This resulted in STUP Consultants handling every aspect of these projects</p>\r\n', '1421906335.jpg', '1421757988.jpg', 'vertical', 'energy-telecommunication-and-space-infrastructure', '2015-01-05 11:10:26', '2015-01-22 18:51:12', '1', '', '', '', 3),
(5, 'Roads, Highways, Expressways', '<p>\r\n	The Indian Road Network started expanding after the development road map was formulated at the Indian Road Congress session in Nagpur in 1956, christened as the &lsquo;Nagpur Plan&rsquo;.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The interstate network and strategically important roads were defined as &ldquo;National Highway&rdquo; and were made the responsibility of the Central Government. Ministry of Surface Transport (MOST) started appointing consultants for coping with the increased volume of work and assumed the role of approving agency. With little previous experience available with Consultants, development of consultancy in this sector was slow. The initial efforts of STUP to participate in Road projects were thwarted as MOST viewed STUP as an organization specialized mainly in Bridges and Structures. While a few medium size Road jobs were handled by STUP under MOST and for the State Governments, it was planned to handle Road Projects on a global platform.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In order to expand business in the Infrastructure sector, STUP started interaction with ADB for obtaining work in other Asian countries. The first success in the Road sector came with the assignment for preparation of Road Master Plan for Bangladesh in the year 1988-89 under ADB with co-financing by the World Bank. Satisfactory completion of the Master Plan was followed by an assignment to prioritize 45000 km of Kabupaten (District) Roads in Java and Bali. STUP completed the task with satisfactory results.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	These two landmark projects earned strong credentials for STUP in the Highway sector and operations in India in this sector increased rapidly. In the first lot of World Bank funded 4 laning projects for National Highways in India in 1994, STUP was successful in all three states &ndash; Haryana, Punjab and Orissa, chosen by the World Bank. These three projects, in association with international consultants, SMEC of Australia, Sauti of &nbsp;Italy and Hyder Freeman Fox of UK respectively, &nbsp;involved 4-laning of existing 2-lane National Highways for a total of about 150 km. Exposure to Consultants across the world helped STUP to consolidate its presence in the Highway Sector. Ever since, STUP has been working in Highways for the National Highways Authority of India, various State level Agencies for development of State Highways and also for Rural Roads under PMGSY programme.</p>\r\n', '1421906393.jpg', '1421758006.jpg', 'horizontal', 'roads-highways-expressways', '2015-01-05 11:12:35', '2015-01-22 18:51:21', '1', '', '', '', 5),
(6, 'Bridges & Flyovers', '<p>\r\n	STUP Consultants Pvt. Ltd. (STUP) was created in 1963 at Mumbai and from the beginning, it started engineering Bridges and some other important Prestressed Concrete Structures. &nbsp;Given below are some of the latest Bridges designed by STUP</p>\r\n', '1421906439.jpg', '1421758089.jpg', 'horizontal', 'bridges-and-flyovers', '2015-01-05 11:13:15', '2015-01-22 18:51:32', '1', '', '', '', 6),
(7, 'Metros', '<p class="STUPMetro">\r\n	<span style="line-height: 18.3999996185303px;">Trend of urbanization and rapid growth of population and vehicular traffic in congested cities have made implementation of Rapid Transit System essential. Construction of Metro Rail, as part of RTS has become imperative for smooth transportation and speedy movement. Metro Rail moves in dedicated tracks going underground or overground avoiding traffic congestion through segregation and priority, reliable with higher carrying capacity and does not spew out noxious fumes. Considering these advantages after Kolkata and Delhi more cities in India are going ahead with installation of Metro Rail Transport.</span></p>\r\n<p class="STUPMetro">\r\n	<span style="line-height: 18.3999996185303px;">SCPL has rendered consultancy on Metro rail projects about two decades back on rehabilitation of distressed section for Kolkata Metro Rail and elevated Metro Rail for MTP Chennai. However STUP got involved in Metro Rail sector more extensively since stage II development of Delhi Metro (DMRC), when DMRC allowed Design Build Contracts.</span></p>\r\n<p class="STUPMetro">\r\n	<span style="line-height: 18.3999996185303px;">The Consultancy services provided for Metro Railway in different Metro Cities of India :</span></p>\r\n<p class="STUPMetro">\r\n	<u><strong><span style="line-height: 18.3999996185303px;">1.</span><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="line-height: 18.3999996185303px; white-space: pre;"> </span><span style="line-height: 18.3999996185303px;">Delhi Metro</span></strong></u></p>\r\n<p class="STUPMetro">\r\n	<span style="line-height: 18.3999996185303px;">a.<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Elevated Viaduct - 17.00 Km.</span></p>\r\n<p class="STUPMetro">\r\n	<span style="line-height: 18.3999996185303px;">b.<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Elevated Station - 9 Nos.</span></p>\r\n<p class="STUPMetro">\r\n	<span style="line-height: 18.3999996