(8, 'Railways', '<p class="STUPMetro" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0cm;line-height:normal;mso-hyphenate:none">\r\n	<span style="font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">Railways are the time tested means of transport specially for long distance with high carrying capacity. Railways have separate tracks for uninterrupted movement which helps to attain high speed. Continuous engineering research and input are helping to develop railway system with higher speed as well higher haulage capacity. This has necessitated review and redesign of trackwork and existing railway bridges. Railway tracks have to move along plain and rolling country as well as hilly terrains. This long traverse needs railway tracks, bridges and tunnels to cross wide rivers, deep gorges and linking through deep rock profiles of hills. Railway Bridges of various forms to suit the topography and site condition have all along been challenging because of the technical attention, it demands in innovative design, construction and erection methodology. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class="STUPMetro" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0cm;line-height:normal;mso-hyphenate:none">\r\n	<span style="font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">SCPL has over the years built up expertise in planning of overall railway system comprising of design of railway trackwork and permanentway , high embankments with slope stability analysis, bridges, associated railway infrastructure like station buildings, locomotive sheds, water supply, electrical, plants for production of railway accessories eg. wheels and axles, deep wagon tipplers for unloading of railway wagons, rehabilitation of railway structures.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class="STUPMetro" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0cm;line-height:normal;mso-hyphenate:none">\r\n	<span style="font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">Some of the major railway projects where SCPL has rendered consultancy services are :<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class="STUPMetro" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:0cm;line-height:normal;mso-hyphenate:none">\r\n	<span style="font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;"><span style="mso-tab-count:4">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class="STUPMetro" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:54.0pt;text-indent:-36.0pt;line-height:normal;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\nmso-hyphenate:none">\r\n<!--[if !supportLists]-->	<span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;"><span style="mso-list:Ignore">A.<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">Trackwork :</span></b><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class="STUPMetro" style="margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:90.0pt;text-indent:-36.0pt;line-height:normal;mso-list:l0 level2 lfo1;\r\nmso-hyphenate:none">\r\n<!--[if !supportLists]-->	<span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;