argin-bottom:6.0pt;\r\nmargin-left:90.0pt;text-indent:-36.0pt;line-height:normal;mso-list:l0 level2 lfo1;\r\nmso-hyphenate:none">\r\n<!--[if !supportLists]-->	<span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;"><span style="mso-list:Ignore">f.<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">Bridges from Vaitarna to Utran on Western Dedicated Freight Corridor Corporation (DFCC )<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n', '1421906466.jpg', '1421758129.jpg', 'horizontal', 'railways', '2015-01-05 11:14:00', '2015-01-22 18:51:45', '1', '', '', '', 7),
(9, 'Offshore, Harbour and Coastal Engineering', '<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	The company has an unparalleled relevance to Offshore, Harbour &amp; Costal Engineering in the developing countries, because of its holistic approach which combines state of the art design techniques, with construction engineering devoted to fully utilizing locally available human and material resources. This involves adapting or creating innovative new methods of construction in developing corresponding construction equipment which suits the local construction environment and includes the training of contractors and owners&rsquo; personnel to successfully use these innovative methods thus creating new and lasting construction traditions relevant to each country. One of the basic factors that contributed to the success of these projects was the deep involvement of Stup Consultants &amp; its determination to stand by them from inception to completion. This resulted in Stup Consultants handling a large range of projects.&nbsp;</p>', '1421906544.jpg', '1421758150.jpg', 'horizontal', 'offshore-harbour-and-coastal-engineering', '2015-01-05 11:14:44', '2015-01-24 09:34:08', '1', '', '', '', 10),
(10, 'Water Resources and Agricultural Development', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify">\r\n	The National water policy adopted in 1987 lays down the broad principles that govern the management of the nation&rsquo;s water resources. The policy recognizes that water is a scarce and precious national resource to be planned, developed and conserved and water resources available to the country should be brought within the category of utilizable resources to the maximum possible extent. Further water resources should be made available to water short areas by transfer from other areas including transfer from one river basin to another river basin. National Water Policy (2002) envisages that the water resources of the country should be developed and managed in an integrated manner.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n	<o:p>&nbsp;</o:p><span style="text-align: justify;">Water resource systems can be created in a number of ways through different combinations of system inputs, levels of output, allocation of reservoir space for different uses, operating rules etc. The optimisation of water use is achieved through maximisation of net benefits.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify">\r\n	<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify">\r\n	<o:p>&nbsp;</o:p>The Water Resources group deals with the&nbsp; Design of storage structures (Gravity Dams and Earth fill dams) and Distribution Systems, Barrages, Water Conductor Systems, Command Area&nbsp; Developments, Lift Irrigation Schemes, Flood Mitigation Works, Hydro Power Projects and Modernisation of Canals and Distribution Systems. Water Storage and utility structures need specific studies in respect to availability of natural resources and optimum use for the betterment and survival of mankind and live stock use. This is a great contribution to the country as a whole and fulfils the objective set by the Government of India, by adopting a common National water policy.</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify">\r\n	<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n', '1421906492.jpg', '1421758179.jpg', 'vertical', 'water-resources-and-agricultural-development', '2015-01-05 11:15:14', '2015-01-22 18:51:54', '1', '', '', '', 8),
(11, 'Construction Engineering, Project Management and Technology Transfer.', '<p>\r\n	Since its inception, STUP Consultants has developed expertise both in Project Management as well as Construction Technology in a wide range of projects to include:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Bridges &amp; National Highways&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Architectural Projects such as townships, industrial structures, institutional &nbsp; &nbsp;buildings, stadiums,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Water resource projects such as Reservoirs, Aqueducts&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Environmental Projects such as effluent treatment plants</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Marine Projects such as Jetties &amp; Offshore Projects&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Rehabilitation Projects</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	These unique structures were distinguished by the utilization of well-adapted new technologies paying particular attention to the use of local resources, effecting substantial savings in cost and high functional and aesthetic values. One of the basic factors that contributed towards the success of these projects was the deep involvement of STUP Consultants and its determination to stand by them from inception to completion. This resulted in STUP Consultants handling every aspect of these projects.</p>\r\n', '1421906570.jpg', '1421758287.jpg', 'horizontal', 'construction-engineering-project-management-and-technology-transfer', '2015-01-05 11:15:36', '2015-01-22 18:54:19', '1', '', '', '', 11),
(12, 'Rehabilitation of Structures and Heritage Buildings', '<p>\r\n	STUP Consultants Pvt. Ltd. has implemented repair &amp; rehabilitation projects for major structures since 1977. A number of major structures constructed in RCC and prestressed concrete in the 1960s and 1970s have been prone to distress due to the materials available at the time as well as the methods of design and construction. The approach of STUP for rehabilitation projects is to carry out a scientific programme of inspection testing and investigations. A visual inspection, reveals data about cracks, leaching &amp; staining of concrete. A dimensional survey is carried out to verify design conformity and to arrive at the self weight of the structure. A geometric survey pinpoints any unusual deflections, differential settlements etc. Detailed tests such as carbonation test, half cell potentiometer for survey, concrete resisting tests, endoscopic examination of prestressing ducts yield valuable information about the present state and potential of ongoing corrosion of reinforcing and prestressing steel. Tests such as rebound hammer test, ultrasonic pulse velocity test, crushing strength on cores establish the present strength of concrete and amenability to external prestressing. Complete chemical analysis of concrete establishes the contamination by external pollutants and the likely residual life of the structure. Based on the scientific programme of investigation, testing and inspection a rehabilitation scheme is prepared to extend the useful life of the structure within the parameters of economic viability. STUP has organised investigation and prepared rehabilitation schemes for major and minor structures belonging to all disciplines mentioned on the previous page. This includes all kinds of structures such as bridges, aqueducts,cooling towers, buildings, heritage buildings, post disaster rehabilitatoin of entire villages, etc.</p>\r\n', '1421906585.jpg', '1421758320.jpg', 'horizontal', 'rehabilitation-of-structures-and-heritage-buildings', '2015-01-05 11:15:55', '2015-01-22 18:54:44', '1', '', '', '', 12);
